The paper focuses on Optical Character Recognition (OCR) using Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) implemented in Tensorflow, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of pretraining and voting techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Connectionist Temporal Classification (CTC) algorithm, which is a deep learning technique (cs.DL).
